field.value:
The "additionalSources" attribute of viewEngine config is loaded but never actually used

My Config

    <viewEngine
      viewPathRoot=""
      customEngine="Castle.MonoRail.Framework.Views.NVelocity.NVelocityViewEngine, Castle.MonoRail.Framework.Views.NVelocity">
      <additionalSources>
        <assembly name="MonoRailUtils" namespace="MonoRailUtils.Views"/>
        <assembly name="Diagnostics" namespace="Diagnostics.Views"/>
      </additionalSources>
    </viewEngine>


The Fix

Inside Service(IServiceProvider provider), assign the sources from ViewEngineConfig to additionalSources (which must be non-readonly). Here's the complete method

		public void Service(IServiceProvider provider)
		{
			MonoRailConfiguration config = (MonoRailConfiguration) provider.GetService(typeof(MonoRailConfiguration));

			if (config != null)
			{
				viewRootDir = config.ViewEngineConfig.ViewPathRoot;
                additionalSources = config.ViewEngineConfig.Sources;
			}
		}
